      • isRejections

        @Deprecated
public boolean isRejections()
        Deprecated. Source file must not know if it matches a convention for specific types, such as rejections. Use RejectionsFile instead.
        Returns true if the source file matches conventions for rejection files.

        A valid rejections file must:

        • be named ending on “rejections.proto”;
        • have the java_multiple_files option set to false;
        • either have a java_outer_classname value which ends with RejectionType.isValidOuterClassName(SimpleClassName) “Rejections”}, or not have the java_outer_classname option set at all.
